FBIS4-15579 "drsov069_r_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 Azerbaijan `Source': Baku Has no Plans To Withdraw from CIS `Source': Baku Has no Plans To Withdraw from CIS LD1004164494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1515 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004164494 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] All speculations about Azerbaijan's plans to withdraw from the CIS, to be announced during the CIS summit on April 15, are unfounded, an informed source in the Azerbaijani president staff told Interfax, commenting on an article in the Moscow newspaper Kommersant (April 8, 1994). "The authors seem to be engaged in wishful thinking. In actual fact, Baku's policies differ cardinally form what is said in the article. We are planning to work for putting into operation the CIS mechanism of curbing external and internal aggressors," he said.
